annotation.TEXT: Well, that big yin-yang orb to the face was pretty rude. It was probably meant to filter out my reserve power up, but...
Oh, pudding, no! She fires evil homing bullets... er, amulets at me as well! Why are you so angry, Reimu? I donated all 3 coins the level gave me...
So, in other words, they're openly admitting to cheap level design now. Anyway... Umm...
Oof! Well, I got it in at least.
So, in other words, if too many enemies spawn at once, a sprite memory issue will make some of them invisible. Anyway, it's boss time, against Reimu herself!
Now, I believe those black blocks are instant death, so I definitely want to avoid them. Also, avoid the munchers, obviously.
Whoa, big bouncing yin-yang orb. I wonder if it's safe to spin jump on...
BGM: Sonic 1 - Spring Yard Zone
Yep... Also, as you can hear, I replaced the vanilla SMW boss music again, and I decided not to bother with the sound channel disabling thing this time.
MEGA KILL!
Reimu: "Dooonaaatiooons! Please! Dooonaaatiooons! Just four or five and there'll be no argument from me!" Step on turtles to turn them into smiling coins. Get three of those into the donation box!
Whoa! Okay, I definitely want to miss these "coins"! ...Or rather, I want them to miss me!
BGM: Seiken Densetsu 3 - Decision Bell
Goal tape average so far: 684 / 21 = 32.571 stars each.
Demo count: 16
Okay, fine. I won't open levels with an immediate pause anymore, at least until the next time I get cheaply ambushed.
Bonk. Yep, a normal stomp works just fine on the yin-yang orbs.
Lucky timing with that spin jump there.
Whoa. I should deal with these quickly, before the next thing spawns, in order to avoid the stealthy sprite memory issue that I was warned about.

Reimu: "Marisa... If you're going to play such games with me, work a little harder and donate more!" If you don't get rid of the attacks and enemies Reimu throws quickly, the next one might go all stealthy on you. However, the white bullets can't be destroyed.
Ah, there's the last smiley coin.
Whoa, that was close.
Okay, clearing that level allowed me access to this castle. And, since I've only been playing for about 5 minutes so far, I think I'll take on this castle now!
I wonder why it was so cheap? Anyway, I've finally finished off Morton here, who appeared to take 7 hits to defeat.
For whatever reason, this level ends with a normal goal point, instead of just ending automatically with Reimu's defeat. I'm fine with that.
Aw, the game made me small again! I'm getting sick of these power up filters.
And here we have yet another power up filter. Also, I didn't cut out the castle music here since it doesn't play for long enough to get claimed.
Yeah, I hate how the camera tends to not scroll to the right of the player very well while you're ballooning.
There's a Goomba. I'll just toss that back at her.
Whoa, good thing I landed hits with all three of them, or I would've been doomed.
I managed to reach it with the left+right glitch just as I got to the spot where I'm supposed to stop riding it. Oh, well.
Death Cave (Hard)
Since this is Hard, you got turned small and your reserve got emptied. Now to fight a powered-up original boss. Must have gone to train at a dojo or something.
Anyway, these Mario Paint smileys are just like footballs and can be stomped.
Well, actually, if that Koopa had hit me, I might've been able to reach this block and get its balloon during my mercy invincibility, so maybe I would've survived.
This Spiny, on the other hand, has been embiggened, but I don't think that's the boss either. Also, we've got a bunch of those unmarked hidden coin blocks here.
There's Goomba #2.
To be continued... Ze! (Also, it's been a while since I ended an episode with me going jittery with the overworld camera!)
BTW, a couple weeks ago, I happened to glance at the used DS games at GameStop, and I noticed The Legendary Starfy was just $2, so I decided to buy it on the spot.
Pfft. Failed on that side. (It would've been a Koopa shell anyway.)
Aha! A Birdo was right there waiting to ambush me! But my cape has something to say about that!
Nah, that guy seemed normal to me.
Bam! The third Goomba to her feet finished the job!
Alright, there's the last Yoshi coin, and I guess that pentagram will warp me to the boss fight, right?
Oh, but they're slide-killable, so I can just sit on this escalator safely.
BGM: Freedom Planet - Boss 1
I imagine that these Boomerang Bros. would be much trickier if it weren't for the slowdown.
Aha! Wings! Too bad this is a no Yoshi level.
No Yoshis because they're still stuck trying to get into Yoshi Village in Winter (Normal).
Am I stuck? These stripes filter out my cape, and I think I was supposed to ride a Birdo egg here...
Close call there. I thought that Koopa was going to nick the extreme corner of my foot's hitbox, which I think would've been deadly for me here.

In the Hard stages, invisible coinblocks aren't marked by coins below. There could be as many of those things as the level designer pleases. In this stage, all the ? blocks contain P-Balloons. You're free to get irritated if you please.
DOUBLE KILL! Aw, I missed one.
And I knew that shell was coming there, since I heard it just a few seconds earlier. So, balloons are in every block, right? But what if I were to do some block cloning?
Actually, these evil homing amulets have been quite manageable so far...
And, yeah, I'm getting slowdown here... Also, I think we've just started autoscrolling vertically.
Ha. Dodged that Pokey.
So, that's why there's no sound effects. Also, Morton has more than 3 HP this time.
Wait, I just noticed that I only had 2 bonus stars before getting that 40. I should've had 44 instead. I think one of the recent HP systems might've replaced my star count.
I'm gonna just circle around and approach that Sledge Bro. from above the coin blocks.
...Yeah, it was easy enough for me to retrieve my reserve cape there. However, being big while ballooning is a disadvantage, so I'll duck-jump into the balloon here.
Hakurei Castle (Hard)
BGM: Touhou 7.5 - Maiden's Capriccio
Oh, man. Diagonal bullets.
No Yoshis because they got Christmas busted for trying to sneak into Yoshi Village in Winter (Normal).
BTW, I'm not concerned with missing a few coins here and there.
MULTI KILL!
D'oh! I wonder if I can get up there and tip it in...
Okay, so we've got Morton, with Bullet Bills added. Umm... If you spin jump on Bullet Bills here, this graphical glitch happens.
In addition, I think the sprite limit prevented that one's boomerang from appearing.
I wonder if more of these things are supposed to be firing those big yin-yang orbs at me.
Well, that's a bummer.
Oh, and I apparently passed 1½ million points during that fight.
Aw, the game arbitrarily decided to filter out my bigness there anyway... But, there's midpoint, which'll embiggen me again.
Yeah, that bullet just went right through my head. However, since I'm still ducking, my hitbox doesn't go that high.
There's a Parakoopa. Let's carefully stomp him without losing his smiley-coin shell to the lava.
Ooh, the next level has two exits. So, how deadly will this Death Cave be? And, will you guys finally get a chance to vote again? Find out next time!
Hello, and welcome back to Scarlet Devil Mario! Let's begin the hard world, with Hakurei Shrine (Hard) here... Oh, and I'm gonna pause immediately upon entering.
There sure are a lot of hidden coin blocks in a row here...
Oh, my spin jump destroyed it. That implies that I can safely stomp it normally. Oh, man. More of those evil homing amulets...
Oh, no! Nononononono! Not these evil things! AAAHHH!!!
That's the last Yoshi coin, so the final Koopduder should be coming up soon.
Come on... Open this block already.
Almost got boiled there, but typically, the bubbly surface tiles of the lava are actually harmless, and it's only the solid red tiles below that are deadly.
Yep, there we go.
Powered-up original boss? Are you talking about this Sledge Brother?
BGM: The Legendary Starfy - Boss Battle
Wait, Reimu's asking for 4 or 5, but the game is instructing us to just toss in 3?
Oh, whoops. I think I was supposed to hitch a ride on that egg while in balloon form. Come back, egg!
Alright, that's one.
